# Terms 
Rendering Strategies:
Client-Side Rendering (CSR): Browser builds the page. Fast updates, slower initial load
- React, Vue, Angular, Svelte

Server-Side Rendering (SSR): Server builds the page. Fast initial load, slower updates
- Languages: JS, Python, Ruby, PHP
- Framework: Next.js, Nuxt.js, Ruby on Rails, Express.js

Static Site Generation (SSG): Pre-built pages. Very fast, but content can be outdated
- Languages: HTML, JS, Markdown
- Framework: Hugo, Next.js (with static export)

Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR): Pre-built pages updates periodiclly. Fast, fresher content
- Languages: JS
- Framework: Next.js (specifically supports ISR)

Stateful: Remembers user context for personalization; more complex to manage
Stateless: Each request is independent; no stored context. Easier to scale

